meta {
  name: GET charging profiles (v2.10.0 Group B)
  type: http
  seq: 44
}

get {
  url: {{base_url}}/v1/vehicles/{{vin}}/charging/profiles
  body: none
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

headers {
  Accept: application/json
}

docs {
  v2.10.0 Group B - SEAT/CUPRA charging profile list.

  Returns the user-configured charging profiles plus the
  ``currentVehiclePositionProfile`` block telling us which profile
  is active right now based on the car's GPS position. SEAT/CUPRA
  flavour of the Skoda profiles endpoint we already parse since
  v1.16.0; we reuse the same coordinator helper
  ``_parse_charging_profiles`` so the resulting field surface is
  identical:

  - ``active_charging_profile_name`` (string)
  - ``active_charging_profile_target_soc_pct`` (int)
  - ``next_charging_time`` (string)
  - ``charging_profiles_count`` (int)
  - ``charging_profiles`` (list - lives in extra_state_attributes)

  Endpoint reference: Timwun/Cupra-WeConnect-Bruno-Collection
  (Charging Profiles sequence), independently parsed in
  ``seat_cupra.get_status`` v2.10.0.

  Response shape (verified against myskoda + pycupra references,
  cross-brand identical):
    {
      "chargingProfiles": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "name": "Home",
          "settings": {
            "maxChargingCurrent": "MAXIMUM" | "REDUCED",
            "targetStateOfChargeInPercent": 80,
            "autoUnlockPlugWhenCharged": "PERMANENT" | "ON" | "OFF"
          },
          "preferredChargingTimes": [...],
          "timers": [...],
          "location": {"latitude": 47.39, "longitude": 8.21} | null
        },
        ...
      ],
      "currentVehiclePositionProfile": {
        "id": 1,
        "name": "Home",
        "targetStateOfChargeInPercent": 80,
        "nextChargingTime": "22:00"
      } | null
    }

  Soft-fails to ``{}`` on 401 / 403 / 404.
}
